  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing ZUS Registration Deadline</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You must register with ZUS within 7 days of registering your JDG business. Missing this deadline can result in penalties and complications. Mark the date and register promptly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Claiming Ulga na Start</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">First-time freelancers can save hundreds of euros by claiming the 6-month startup relief. It must be claimed when registering—you can't claim it retroactively. Ensure your accountant includes this in your registration.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Hiring an Accountant</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Polish tax and ZUS obligations are complex. DIY bookkeeping often leads to errors, penalties, and missed deductions. The €50-150/month for an accountant is essential—not optional.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing Temporary Residence Application</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You must apply for a temporary residence permit within 45 days of arrival. The Type D visa is just for entry—you need the residence permit for legal long-term stay. Don't delay this application.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting DNV-Style Simplicity</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Poland's system requires full business integration—registration, tax obligations, ZUS contributions. If you want minimal paperwork and no local ties, Poland isn't the right choice. Consider Hungary or Croatia instead.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

