    <p class="mb-4">
      Poland's freelance visa isn't for everyone—it requires full business integration, ZUS contributions, and local tax obligations. But for freelancers willing to embrace the system, it offers unique advantages: work with any clients (Polish or foreign), path to permanent residency, and no strict income minimum.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The ZUS relief programs (Ulga na start, Mały ZUS) make the first 2.5 years very affordable, and Poland's growing tech scene offers opportunities for building a local client base. Warsaw, Kraków, and Wrocław have vibrant startup ecosystems and established expat communities.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-6">
